results.name: Numbers that are the sum of 4 positive cubes in exactly 1 way.
link: Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Cubic Number.
mathematica: Reap[For[n = 1, n <= 300, n++, pr = Select[ PowersRepresentations[n, 4, 3], Times @@ # != 0 &]; If[pr != {} && Length[pr] == 1, Print[n, pr]; Sow[n]]]][[2, 1]] (* _Jean-François Alcover_, Jul 31 2013 *)
xref: Cf. A003327 (1 or more ways), A025399 (three distinct cubes).
results.author: _David W. Wilson_
